AB  - This paper derives theoretical Ecu yields from its basket construction. Covered interest-rate parity is used to revise the weights of currencies in the basket over time. The result reconciles theory with the observation that in the market the Ecu yield curve's slope is distinctly less than a basket average with constant weights. Equipped with this fundamental result, the paper then derives results for Ecu interest rates of variations in interest and exchange rates of component currencies, and of Ecu basket revisions.
ER  - 
